Quote: STRONG winds and a heavy swell at the weekend helped dissipate huge stretches of mud-like growth which has drastically reduced Taranaki fishing catches.  Nicknamed grey mud or the dreaded lurgy, the growth has stretched from Mokau, 70 kilometres northwest of Waitara, to Cape Egmont.
